Present Perfect 1
1.
1) He has cleaned his shoes.
2) She has closed the door.
3) They have gone to bed.
4) It has stopped raining.
5) He has had a shower.
6) The picture has fallen down.
2.
1) I've lost my keys. I don't know where they are.
2) I have bought some new shoes.
3) Where is Helen? She has gone out.
4) I'm looking for Paula. Have you seen her?
5) Look! Somebody has broken that window.
6) Does Lisa know that you're going away? Yes, I've told her.
7) I can't find my umbrella. Somebody has taken it.
8) Where are my glasses? I don't know. I haven't seen it.
9) I'm looking for Sarah. Where has she gone?
10) I know that woman, but I've forgotten her name.
11) Sue is have a party tonight. She has invited a lot of people.
12) What are you going to do? Have you decided?
13) I haven't told him.
14) I've finished with this magazine. Do you want it?
3.
1) Ann has gone to bed.
2) Kim isn't at work. She has gone/leaved on holiday.
3) I've lost my credit card.
4) We've bought a new sofa.
5) Where is Garry? Have you seen him?
6) I'm busy. I haven't finished my work/job.
7) I met that man before, but I've forgotten his name.
8) Look! Somebody has broken the window.